    {
        "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1720163805.536149",
        "client_msg_id": "0291bd1c-4d94-447e-8d1a-6d73f5db3216",
        "text": "We could start by adopting some chat/forum that we consider open and stable enough that it's worth building on its API. And then slowly, and ideally collectively, build the Wiki and bot parts. Maybe explore different directions in parallel.\n\nOne reason I believe it's worth an effort, and a reason why I'd be happy to join such a project, is that it's not just us. I participate in two other communities that are wondering about the same questions. But those communities are not about software, so there's little in-house competence to draw on. If _we_ can't scratch our own itches, then who can?",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "thread_ts": "1720065086.549499",
        "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "vIaT3",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "We could start by adopting some chat/forum that we consider open and stable enough that it's worth building on its API. And then slowly, and ideally collectively, build the Wiki and bot parts. Maybe explore different directions in parallel.\n\nOne reason I believe it's worth an effort, and a reason why I'd be happy to join such a project, is that it's not just us. I participate in two other communities that are wondering about the same questions. But those communities are not about software, so there's little in-house competence to draw on. If "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "we",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
