                                "text": "I guess I wouldn't have written this before my Smalltalk experience over the last five years. The main lesson I learned from other Smalltalkers is the value of growing software rather than designing it, if it is for your own use (no contracts, no marketing people, ...). You start with the simplest thing that can possibly work (a phrase due to Ward Cunningham), and then you start using it to find out where you really want to go."
